#antispam #onboarding #tenant #email 
Go to Tenant> Security> Policies & Rules > Threat Policies > Anti Spam > Hover over words and click Anti-Spam outbound policy > Click edit protection settings > set email to [support@go2rcg.com](mailto:support@go2rcg.com) > Click Save  - Note: (It will prompt you to enable organization customization, once approved it can take up to 24 hours for the setting to take effect, you will have to re add the email and save once the setting is enabled). 

Enable-OrganizationCustomization

​ 

1. Go into Tenant > Show All 

![Go into Tenant > Show All](data:image/png;base64,) 

2. Choose Security 

![Choose Security](data:image/png;base64,) 

3. Click Policies & Rules 

![Click Policies & Rules](data:image/png;base64,) 

4. Click Threat Policies 

![Click Threat Policies](data:image/png;base64,) 

5. Click Anti-spam 

![Click Anti-spam](data:image/png;base64,) 

6. Hover over Anit-spam outbound policy default and click 

![Hover over Anit-spam outbound policy default and click](data:image/png;base64,) 

7. Brings up a window > click on Edit protection settings. 

![Brings up a window > click on Edit protection settings.](data:image/png;base64,) 

8. Enter support@go2rcg.com 

![Enter support@go2rcg.com](data:image/png;base64,) 

9. Click Save 

![Click Save](data:image/png;base64,) 

It will prompt you to enable organization customization, once approved it can take up to 24 hours for the setting to take effect, you will have to re add the email and save once the setting is enabled.
